Trail Activity Lexicon

Overview

This page contains the text analysis tools for working with texts related to trails and nature experiences. This lexicon includes terms related to trails and nature experiences that have been tagged for themes. These themes are further grouped into broader themes at multiple levels. The tagged terms are drawn from an online survey of trail users and trail maintainers who were asked to freelist the types of activities people do on trails. Based on these text responses, individual terms were tagged for future use in term-based text analysis. This domain-specific lexicon is shared here as a baseline for future research into text analytics related to trails and protected areas.

Lexicon csv

Lexicon structure

Word Tag Category Theme
Words related to trails, nature experiences, and outdoor recreation. This includes a list of 800 tagged terms. Some of the terms are tagged with more than one tag, for a total of 597 unique terms. Tags at the most specific level. This includes tags such as sight, forage, and discovery. There are a total of 41 tags. Categories combine tags into more general groups. Categories include groups such as outdoor skills, learn, and health. There are a total of 18 categories. Themes are the broadest level of grouping terms. Themes include individual, social, and action. There are a total of 5 themes.

The figure below displays the structure of the lexicon in an interactive graphic. Each color represents a different level of the taggig lexicon. Click on the circles to move between the levels and see the terms included in each subset.
